>Step 5: Add salt and pepper to taste.<br><hr>Step 6: OPTIONAL: Slice an avocado, remove the pit, and serve the chicken salad with avocado. It\'s so good! <br><hr>'),
(183, 648883, 'meat', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/648883-312x231.jpg', '45', 'Non-Veg', 'Kidney Pie', 'Kidney Pie could be just the <b>dairy free</b> recipe you\'ve been looking for. This recipe serves 1 and costs 67 cents per serving. One serving contains <b>279 calories</b>, <b>8g of protein</b>, and <b>1g of fat</b>. 1 person were impressed by this recipe. Head to the store and pick up potatoes, veal kidney, flour, and a few other things to make it today. It is brought to you by Foodista. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly <b>45 minutes</b>. Overall, this recipe earns an <b>awesome spoonacular score of 88%</b>. Users who liked this recipe also liked <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/steak-and-kidney-pie-1091218\">Steak and Kidney Pie</a>, <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/steak-kidney-pie-1090328\">Steak & Kidney Pie</a>, and <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/a-good-steak-kidney-pie-1211675\">A good steak & kidney pie</a>.', '1 beef bouillon cube<br><hr>1/2 cup sliced carrots, cooked<br><hr>2 tablespoons flour<br><hr>1 small onion, chopped<br><hr>1 cup cubed potatoes, cooked<br><hr>1 salt and pepper<br><hr>1 veal kidney<br><hr>1/4 cup cold water<br><hr>', 'Step 1: First wash the kidney well. Cover with cold water and let stand for about an hour.<br><hr>Step 2: Drain.<br><hr>Step 3: Remove the cords and all of the center fat.<br><hr>Step 4: Cut into small pieces. Now combine the bouillon cube and boiling water.<br><hr>Step 5: Add the chopped kidney. Simmer for 20 minutes.<br><hr>Step 6: Combine the flour and cold water, mixing well; add to the kidney mixture, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.<br><hr>Step 7: Add the cooked vegetables, and season to taste with salt and pepper.<br><hr>Step 8: Pour mixture into a baking dish, and cover with small baking powder biscuits or pastry dough.<br><hr>Step 9: Bake at 400F.<br><hr>');
